CSL
Cognitive Specification Language

Copyright (c) 2026
Keyla Avanda

CSL is an independent research project exploring
modular behavioral architecture for AI systems.

Rather than describing intelligence through a
single prompt, CSL separates intrinsic identity,
extrinsic environment, and runtime decision-making
into composable behavioral specifications.

Python serves only as the host language.

CSL itself is the behavioral specification.

If you build something interesting with CSL,
I'd genuinely love to hear about it.